## Project Description

---

This project involves designing a table-top assistive robotic arm to help individuals with limited mobility pick and place small household objects. The arm will be controlled through voice commands or a simple joystick, using Arduino for motor control and a Raspberry Pi for speech recognition and processing. The goal is to improve user independence through an affordable and easy-to-use assistive device.

